text:
how to center div inside another div by using tailwind css

To center a `div` inside another `div` using Tailwind CSS, you will typically use a combination of `flex` utilities. Assuming you want to add an inner `div` within the `<div></div>` in your `page.tsx` and center it both horizontally and vertically, you can do so by applying the appropriate Tailwind classes.

Here's how you could update your `page.tsx` to include a centered inner `div`:

```tsx
// import Image from "next/image";

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <main>
      <div className="bg-white m-4 text-2xl p-4">Hello next</div>

      {/* Outer div with flexbox utilities applied for centering */}
      <div className="flex items-center justify-center h-screen">
        {/* Inner div you want to center */}
        <div className="bg-gray-200 p-8 rounded-lg">
          Centered content
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  );
}
```

Explanation:
- The outer `div` uses several classes:
  - `flex`: This applies display flex, enabling flexbox layout to its children.
  - `items-center`: This aligns the children (the inner div) vertically in the center.
  - `justify-center`: This centers the children (the inner div) horizontally.
  - `h-screen`: This gives the outer `div` a height that covers the entire viewport height, providing a clear space for centering. If you do not need the entire height of the viewport, you can adjust this value accordingly or remove it.

- The inner `div` is the content that you want to center. The classes applied to this `div` (`bg-gray-200 p-8 rounded-lg`) are just for visual enhancement and do not affect the centering.
